text: Joanna Ignasiak (born 14 October 1983) is a road cyclist from Poland. She represented her nation at the 2003 UCI Road World Championships. In 2007, she won the Polish National Time Trial Championships. ==References== ==External links== * profile at Procyclingstats.com Category:1983 births Category:Polish female cyclists Category:Living people Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
